data.title: MAFS Australia season 11 release schedule: When is it next on?
data.meta_description: Here's the full episode release schedule of Married At First Sight Australia season 11 and when it's airing in the UK.
data.text:
One of our favourite reality TV series, Married At First Sight Australia, is back on E4 for series 11, bringing more awkward wedding ceremonies, dramatic dinner parties and some sage advice from John, Mel and Alessandra.

For those who haven't seen the series before, or need a refresher on the concept, each series sees a group of singletons paired up by the experts with their best suited match. The couple then meets for the first time on their wedding day at the end of the aisle. They get married, before embarking on their honeymoon, moving in together, meeting each other's friends and family, and sharing their marriage journey with their fellow cast members at weekly dinner parties.

And the new series finally kicked off on E4 at the end of February in the UK, and is expected to run for a number of weeks. So curious when the next episode of MAFS Australia is on? Then here's the full episode release schedule of Married At First Sight Australia season 11.

When did Married At First Sight Australia season 11 premiere?

Season 11 of Married At First Sight Australia first began airing in Australia on 29th January, and us viewers in the UK had to wait nearly a whole month before the series began airing on E4 on 26th February 2024. But, wow, was it worth the wait.

How many MAFS Australia episodes are there?

So far the number of episodes for season 11 of MAFS Australia is yet to be confirmed. However if we look at last season, we're in for a lot of dinner party chaos, as season 10 had a whopping 36 episodes, including the reunion episodes.

The series ran from 30th January to 3rd April 2023 when airing in Australia, so we would imagine series 11 will follow a similar pattern. So for viewers for season 11 in the UK, if we shift this timeline by around a month, the series launched at the end of February 2024 and we can expect it to end at the end of April. So much MAFS.

When does the next episode of Married At First Sight Australia season 11 come out?

Married At First Sight Australia airs on E4 in the UK four nights a week from Monday to Thursday.

Each episode starts at 7:30pm and ends at around 9pm or 9:05pm depending on the length of the episode.

When do episodes of MAFS Australia season 11 arrive on Channel 4 catchup?

If you've missed an episode or switched on the TV half way through you can watch the full episode on catchup on Channel 4 shortly after the episode has aired.

What is the MAFS Australia season 11 release schedule?
